## §4 Three Curated Collections

The Commons Engineering platform is built on three foundational collections. All three are **open source curated pattern collections**, free for anyone to use. cloudsters stewards them; it does not own them.

```
        COMMONS_BLUEPRINT (patterns)
              /              \
             /                \
    COMMONS_ENGINEER ——— COMMONS_OS
    (practitioners)      (operating system)
```

| Collection | What it holds | What it enables | How others might use it differently |
|---|---|---|---|
| **COMMONS_BLUEPRINT** | Patterns — the knowledge library | The design language for living systems | Different taxonomy, different pattern selection for context |
| **COMMONS_ENGINEER** | Practitioners — skills, curriculum, qualification | Practitioner development paths | Completely different curriculum — academic, corporate, self-study |
| **COMMONS_OS** | Operating system patterns — governance, operations, economics | Commons creation and operation | Different operating model, different rhythms, different economics |

The relationship:
- A **pattern** is applied by an **engineer** at a **commons**.
- A **commons** produces **lighthouses** that reference **patterns**.
- An **engineer** belongs to one or more **commons** and works with **patterns**.

Everything else — lighthouses, engagements, signals, blueprints — hangs off these three anchors.

